column1: # These readings were taken from two nearby Hagworthingham village sites, by the same observer, Mr R.Wright.
# i) Before April 1920, the gauge was 200-300 yards north of the church, so somewhere close to the junction midway along Church Lane
# ii) From April 1920, the gauge was at Glebe House, just north of the church (next to the school).
# The grid reference provided is for Glebe House.
# The gauge then moved to the Manor House in February 1935.
